@node sect0 "Name"
iconvctl - control iconv behavior 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"

@{code}#include <iconv.h>
int iconvctl (iconv_t cd , int request, void * argument);@{body}

@endnode

@node sect2 "@{ub}Description"
The argument @{i}cd@{ui} must be a conversion descriptor created using the function @{b}iconv_open@{ub}. @{b}iconvctl@{ub} queries or adjusts the behavior of the @{b}iconv@{ub} function, when invoked with the specified conversion descriptor, depending on the request value. 


@endnode

@node sect3 "Request Values"
The following are permissible values for the @{i}request@{ui} parameter. 

 @{b}ICONV_TRIVIALP@{ub} @{lindent 3}
@{i}argument@{ui} should be an @{b}int *@{ub} which will receive 1 if the conversion is trivial, or 0 otherwise. @{lindent 0}

 @{b}ICONV_GET_TRANSLITERATE@{ub} @{lindent 3}
@{i}argument@{ui} should be an @{b}int *@{ub} which will receive 1 if  transliteration is enabled in the conversion, or 0 otherwise. @{lindent 0}

 @{b}ICONV_SET_TRANSLITERATE@{ub} @{lindent 3}
@{i}argument@{ui} should be a @{b}const int *@{ub}, pointing to an @{b}int@{ub} value. A non-zero value is used to enable transliteration in the conversion. A zero value disables it. @{lindent 0}

 @{b}ICONV_GET_DISCARD_ILSEQ@{ub} @{lindent 3}
@{i}argument@{ui} should be an @{b}int *@{ub} which will receive 1 if  "illegal sequence discard and continue" is enabled in the conversion, or 0 otherwise. @{lindent 0}

 @{b}ICONV_SET_DISCARD_ILSEQ@{ub} @{lindent 3}
@{i}argument@{ui} should be a @{b}const int *@{ub}, pointing to an @{b}int@{ub} value. A non-zero value is used to enable "illegal sequence discard and continue" in the conversion. A zero value disables it. @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect4 "Return Value"
The @{b}iconvctl@{ub} function returns 0 if it succeeds. In case of error, it sets @{b}errno@{ub} and returns -1. 
@endnode

@node sect5 "Errors"
The following errors can occur, among others: 

 @{b}EINVAL@{ub} @{lindent 3}
The request is invalid. @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect6 "Conforming to"
This function is implemented only in GNU libiconv and not in other @{b}iconv@{ub} implementations. It is not backed by a standard. You can test for its presence through @{b}(_LIBICONV_VERSION >= 0x0108)@{ub}. 
@endnode

